A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 42-8-38 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to arrest
2 or graduated sanctions for probationers violating terms, hearing, disposition of charge, and
3 procedure when probation revoked in county other than that of conviction, so as to provide
4 for credit for time served regarding probation revocation sentencing; to provide for related
5 matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Code Section 42-8-38 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to arrest or
9 graduated sanctions for probationers violating terms, hearing, disposition of charge, and
10 procedure when probation revoked in county other than that of conviction, is amended by
11 revising subsection (c) as follows:
12 "(c) After the hearing, the court may revoke, modify, or continue the probation. If the
13 probation is revoked, the court may order the execution of the sentence originally imposed
14 or of any portion thereof. In such event, the time that the defendant has served under
15 probation shall be considered as time served and shall be deducted from and considered a
16 part of the time he or she was originally sentenced to serve. Regarding any carceral
